WEBVTT

00:05.788 --> 00:06.180
.

00:06.223 --> 00:07.572
- I love this theater.

00:07.616 --> 00:09.357
Yeah, great bones, right?

00:09.400 --> 00:10.836
[classical music plays]
Mm-hmm, totally.

00:10.880 --> 00:12.316
I have.

00:12.360 --> 00:14.057
Actually, I was here
opening night.

00:14.101 --> 00:15.145
- Shh.

00:15.189 --> 00:16.538
[whispering]
The show is starting.

00:16.581 --> 00:17.756
- [whispers]
I'm sorry.

00:19.236 --> 00:20.542
- Lights.
- Okay, yeah.

00:20.585 --> 00:21.717
I keep forgetting.

00:21.760 --> 00:25.199
[music continues]

00:25.242 --> 00:31.770
♪

00:48.178 --> 00:49.310
Okay.

00:49.353 --> 00:51.486
I have got a yummy lunch
for you today.

00:51.529 --> 00:53.053
You're gonna be--
[clicks tongue]

00:57.187 --> 00:58.623
Hey, let's practice, okay?

00:59.798 --> 01:02.453
Go.
- My name is Makayla.

01:02.497 --> 01:05.195
- Hi, Makayla. I'm Kimberly.

01:05.239 --> 01:08.894
- You wanna play on the swings
with me?

01:08.938 --> 01:11.419
- I do. You seem very nice.

01:14.161 --> 01:15.597
Okay?

01:17.903 --> 01:19.383
See you tonight.

01:29.611 --> 01:32.092
- Caller reports lawn mower
missing from garage.

01:34.311 --> 01:36.748
Units in the 13th,
calls of a woman down.

01:36.792 --> 01:38.533
221 South Mohawk.

01:38.576 --> 01:40.752
Caller states GSWs
to the head,

01:40.796 --> 01:42.232
possible fall from roof.

01:42.276 --> 01:44.713
[dramatic music]

01:44.756 --> 01:47.672
- 5021 Eddie, plainclothes
officer responding on Mohawk,

01:47.716 --> 01:49.544
- Copy 5021 Eddie.

01:49.587 --> 01:56.594
♪

01:58.205 --> 01:59.597
- Hey.

01:59.641 --> 02:00.685
What do we got?

02:00.729 --> 02:02.252
- Two shots to the head,

02:02.296 --> 02:04.907
execution style.

02:04.950 --> 02:07.431
Somebody took her up
and pop, pop, she fell.

02:07.475 --> 02:10.434
[dramatic music]

02:10.478 --> 02:13.176
♪

02:13.220 --> 02:14.612
- I don't think that's right.

02:14.656 --> 02:16.484
You see that dent?

02:16.527 --> 02:18.486
Look where her body is
compared to where she landed.

02:18.529 --> 02:20.444
And her fingers, look at that.

02:20.488 --> 02:22.577
They're dug in.

02:22.620 --> 02:24.361
I think she survived the fall

02:24.405 --> 02:25.580
and then she was
trying to move.

02:25.623 --> 02:27.277
She was trying to drag herself.

02:27.321 --> 02:30.411
That's when someone
came and popped her.

02:30.454 --> 02:32.282
- We're gonna go ahead and
turn her over if that's okay.

02:32.326 --> 02:33.414
- Yeah, go ahead.

02:33.457 --> 02:40.464
♪

02:40.725 --> 02:41.900
- Ready?

02:45.643 --> 02:47.471
Christ, she's pregnant.

02:47.515 --> 02:49.517
♪

02:49.560 --> 02:51.606
This your homicide?

02:51.649 --> 02:53.390
- Yeah, it's my homicide.

02:53.434 --> 03:00.397
♪

03:00.441 --> 03:01.877
- Gracias.

03:01.920 --> 03:03.008
- We got her fanny pack off.

03:03.052 --> 03:04.184
- Let's take a look.

03:09.493 --> 03:11.365
Sofia Perez.

03:17.632 --> 03:20.243
- What are those?
- They're trouble dolls.

03:20.287 --> 03:21.810
From Guatemala, I think.

03:21.853 --> 03:23.942
Put 'em under your pillow
when you go to sleep

03:23.986 --> 03:25.248
and when you wake up
in the morning,

03:25.292 --> 03:27.903
they've taken away
all your troubles.

03:27.946 --> 03:30.862
- Hey.
- Hey.

03:30.906 --> 03:33.691
Okay, so the DOA
is Sofia Perez.

03:33.735 --> 03:35.563
17, a Guatemalan national.

03:35.606 --> 03:38.696
I'm thinking she was running
from something or someone.

03:38.740 --> 03:40.437
Came down here
to this construction site,

03:40.481 --> 03:41.873
but it's a dead-end.
- Huh.

03:41.917 --> 03:43.135
- I just talked
to that resident.

03:43.179 --> 03:44.963
She heard banging on the door
but she hid.

03:45.007 --> 03:46.530
Thought it was a robber,

03:46.574 --> 03:48.793
so we have Sofia, dead-end,

03:48.837 --> 03:50.012
can't get in the door.

03:50.055 --> 03:52.275
I think she took
the only other option.

03:52.319 --> 03:53.537
- She went up.
- Yeah, she went up

03:53.581 --> 03:55.409
the fire escape to the roof.

03:55.452 --> 03:57.541
Whether she was pushed or fell,

03:57.585 --> 03:59.543
she landed here and
then whoever was chasing her

03:59.587 --> 04:01.763
found her, put two in her head.
Close range.

04:01.806 --> 04:03.025
- Shell casings?
- No.

04:03.068 --> 04:05.332
So either the shooter
policed them himself

04:05.375 --> 04:06.811
or we're looking at
a wheel gun.

04:06.855 --> 04:08.900
- Sarge, security camera
on this building right here

04:08.944 --> 04:10.554
has a pretty good angle.

04:10.598 --> 04:13.557
[tense music]

04:13.601 --> 04:19.389
♪

04:19.433 --> 04:20.869
She's alive.

04:20.912 --> 04:23.045
- All right, let's just
skip to what we need to see.

04:23.088 --> 04:24.307
- All right.

04:24.351 --> 04:27.092
40 seconds later.

04:27.136 --> 04:29.486
- Wait, wait. Freeze it.

04:29.530 --> 04:31.880
All right, zoom in.
- Mm-hmm.

04:31.923 --> 04:34.012
- Anybody recognize that logo?

04:34.056 --> 04:36.363
- Murder weapon's a revolver,
make unknown.

04:36.406 --> 04:38.756
The slugs came back
from the autopsy, .38s.

04:38.800 --> 04:40.932
- Sarge, the street
where Sofia died

04:40.976 --> 04:42.369
is right in the middle
of the claimed turf

04:42.412 --> 04:44.806
of two rival gangs,
Los Milagros and Los Payasos.

04:44.849 --> 04:46.068
- There's been some real beef.

04:46.111 --> 04:47.504
Six murders in three months.

04:47.548 --> 04:48.940
Homicide says
two of those murders

04:48.984 --> 04:50.725
were female drug couriers.

04:50.768 --> 04:53.336
Guatemalan nationals
like our victim, Sofia Perez.

04:53.380 --> 04:56.470
- All right, so good chance
Sofia was a drug mule.

04:56.513 --> 04:57.949
All right, this man
in the video,

04:57.993 --> 05:00.343
let's see if any other cameras
picked him up.

05:00.387 --> 05:02.911
And our victim, I want to
figure out how she got here.

05:02.954 --> 05:04.695
Check ports of entry.

05:04.739 --> 05:06.436
See if she's got
family here in Chicago.

05:06.480 --> 05:08.612
Let's go.

05:08.656 --> 05:12.137
- Play it.
[phone buzzes]

05:12.181 --> 05:16.968
[buzzing]

05:17.012 --> 05:18.492
[sighs]

05:18.535 --> 05:20.102
- Another signature here.
- Okay.

05:20.145 --> 05:21.930
- Everything's moving along
really well.

05:21.973 --> 05:24.454
Your petition to adopt
has been accepted by the court.

05:24.498 --> 05:26.369
I think I told you, we were
able to keep her social--

05:26.413 --> 05:27.805
- Yeah, last time.
- When we can do that,

05:27.849 --> 05:29.416
we leapfrog some steps,

05:29.459 --> 05:31.940
so we were able to issue
a new birth certificate.

05:31.983 --> 05:33.376
The judge still
has to certify it

05:33.420 --> 05:39.034
but here is the provisional.

05:39.077 --> 05:42.472
Next steps, I need you
to select your custodian.

05:42.516 --> 05:43.995
Your backup, so to speak.

05:44.039 --> 05:46.389
- Oh, no.

05:46.433 --> 05:48.435
I'm not going anywhere
anytime soon.

05:48.478 --> 05:50.611
- This is the law, Kim.
Not optional.

05:50.654 --> 05:52.308
You understand,
this is the person

05:52.352 --> 05:54.615
that would take care of Makayla
if something happened to you.

05:54.658 --> 05:56.530
If you died.

05:56.573 --> 05:57.705
Right.

05:57.748 --> 06:00.403
All right, okay.

06:00.447 --> 06:02.971
I'm gonna need a few days
to think about it.

06:06.627 --> 06:08.411
Hey.
- Hey, that drug mule theory's

06:08.455 --> 06:10.892
looking pretty good.
- OCD transpo ran our victim

06:10.935 --> 06:12.415
through inbound flights.

06:12.459 --> 06:14.025
She arrived at O'Hare
three weeks ago,

06:14.069 --> 06:15.505
direct from Guatemala city.

06:15.549 --> 06:17.115
One-way ticket
paid for in cash.

06:17.159 --> 06:18.856
Now, the video footage
shows this guy

06:18.900 --> 06:20.684
finding Sofia at baggage claim.

06:20.728 --> 06:21.990
He walks her out,

06:22.033 --> 06:24.035
he even takes her suitcase
for her.

06:24.079 --> 06:25.776
- Surely just being
a gentleman.

06:25.820 --> 06:28.126
- Right, so the gentleman
takes her to this car.

06:28.170 --> 06:30.955
Plates come back to
an Alex Alonzo, 22 years old.

06:30.999 --> 06:32.957
He's got a different build
from the guy in this video,

06:33.001 --> 06:35.525
but he's documented
Los Milagros for a fact.

06:35.569 --> 06:36.874
- Scoop him up.

06:36.918 --> 06:38.572
Quietly.

06:38.615 --> 06:40.965
Los Milagros.

06:44.273 --> 06:46.884
We know your people bring in
fentanyl through O'Hare.

06:46.928 --> 06:49.147
We've caught you
five or six times.

06:49.191 --> 06:51.062
Probably didn't catch you
the other 30.

06:51.106 --> 06:54.762
- Sir, I don't know--
- Alex, we know.

06:54.805 --> 06:58.548
Kay? You use girls,

06:58.592 --> 07:00.115
young women,

07:00.158 --> 07:02.030
as couriers.

07:02.073 --> 07:03.858
Mules.

07:03.901 --> 07:07.688
See, this time,

07:07.731 --> 07:09.951
this time was different.

07:13.607 --> 07:15.478
This time one of them
got murdered.

07:15.522 --> 07:17.262
- No, I'm nobody.
- Uh-huh.

07:17.306 --> 07:18.655
- I'm a driver, a runner.

07:18.699 --> 07:21.615
- No, no, no,
I'll tell you who you are.

07:21.658 --> 07:24.487
You are her first contact
here in America.

07:24.531 --> 07:27.098
You hearing
what I'm telling you?

07:27.142 --> 07:30.754
You brought the lamb
to the slaughter.

07:30.798 --> 07:32.234
That makes you just as guilty

07:32.277 --> 07:33.670
as the man
who pulled the trigger.

07:33.714 --> 07:35.977
- No, I swear,
they tell me nothing.

07:36.020 --> 07:37.152
I get texted

07:37.195 --> 07:39.154
arrangements from some burner.
- Uh-huh.

07:39.197 --> 07:41.504
- Pick up this person,
bring 'em here.

07:41.548 --> 07:43.201
And my cousin, he gives me
a little cash for it--

07:43.245 --> 07:47.162
- Sofia Perez.

07:47.205 --> 07:48.555
Where did you bring her
after you

07:48.598 --> 07:51.122
picked her up from the airport?

07:51.166 --> 07:55.126
[tense music]

07:55.170 --> 08:01.611
♪

08:01.655 --> 08:02.830
- There's got to be
some answers in there.

08:02.873 --> 08:05.093
When I give a positive,
you guys move.

08:05.136 --> 08:07.617
- Go get 'em.
We got you, Ruz.

08:07.661 --> 08:08.966
We are seven blocks away

08:09.010 --> 08:11.621
from where Sofia Perez
was murdered.

08:11.665 --> 08:15.016
♪

08:15.059 --> 08:16.931
- Hello?

08:16.974 --> 08:23.198
♪

08:23.241 --> 08:24.765
Meter man.

08:24.808 --> 08:31.815
♪

08:44.262 --> 08:47.004
Hello.

08:47.048 --> 08:49.006
Meter man.

08:49.050 --> 08:55.317
♪

08:55.360 --> 08:57.101
I don't think
there's anybody here.

08:59.974 --> 09:02.759
Why don't you come in
that back door.

09:07.895 --> 09:09.940
What the hell?

09:09.984 --> 09:11.638
- [whistles quietly]

09:15.076 --> 09:17.034
Okay.
- I don't know what this is

09:17.078 --> 09:19.210
but it's definitely not
what we were expecting.

09:19.254 --> 09:21.648
- Hell no.

09:21.691 --> 09:23.954
- Let's move towards the back.

09:26.914 --> 09:29.351
Got an open door.

09:39.143 --> 09:41.581
- Clear?
- Yeah.

09:48.413 --> 09:50.067
Clear.

09:52.722 --> 09:55.638
- This food is fresh.

09:55.682 --> 09:58.380
- I got women's clothing,
underwear over here.

09:58.423 --> 10:01.078
- Yo, we got cuffs.

10:01.122 --> 10:03.994
Another room.

10:04.038 --> 10:06.083
- You ready?
- Yeah.

10:06.127 --> 10:09.086
[suspenseful music]

10:09.130 --> 10:16.093
♪

10:16.137 --> 10:17.138
- Christ.

10:25.363 --> 10:27.931
- Babies were born here.

10:29.106 --> 10:30.281
Recently.

10:30.325 --> 10:33.720
♪

10:36.940 --> 10:37.332
.

10:37.375 --> 10:39.682
- Bars on each and
every one of the windows.

10:39.726 --> 10:42.337
Handcuffs on each
and every one of the beds.

10:42.380 --> 10:44.121
- These women lived there,
Sarge,

10:44.165 --> 10:45.427
or were kept there.

10:45.470 --> 10:47.385
- This was never
about narcotics.

10:47.429 --> 10:49.692
I mean, Sofia Perez,
she was running from this.

10:49.736 --> 10:52.216
Some sort of...baby farm.

10:52.260 --> 10:53.914
- Then after they killed her,
they abandoned the place.

10:53.957 --> 10:56.264
- Yeah, 'cause they knew
there'd be heat.

10:56.307 --> 11:00.485
So, who the hell are they?
Where did they go?

11:00.529 --> 11:03.227
And where are the other women?
- Sarge,

11:03.271 --> 11:05.882
forensics ran the dried blood
that we found on a towel,

11:05.926 --> 11:07.449
got a hit on CODIS.

11:07.492 --> 11:09.712
Karla de Leon, 21,
Guatemalan national.

11:09.756 --> 11:12.628
- And she was in there?
- And she had a baby in there.

11:12.672 --> 11:15.544
Forensics found traces
of amniotic fluid, too.

11:15.587 --> 11:16.850
- If I'm right about this,

11:16.893 --> 11:18.765
if these sons of bitches
are selling babies,

11:18.808 --> 11:20.897
once these mothers give birth,

11:20.941 --> 11:23.639
they got no value
to these people anymore.

11:23.683 --> 11:25.510
I mean, if she's still alive,

11:25.554 --> 11:28.818
chances are they just turned
her out on the street, right?

11:28.862 --> 11:31.952
So boots on the ground.
Karla de Leon, let's find her.

11:31.995 --> 11:33.649
- Copy that.

11:33.693 --> 11:37.435
Okay, how do we do that?

11:37.479 --> 11:39.655
- All right, I'm thinking
I'm a young Guatemalan woman.

11:39.699 --> 11:42.614
I'm alone, I'm in trouble.
I'm in a city I don't know.

11:42.658 --> 11:44.616
I find a priest.

11:44.660 --> 11:46.314
I'm gonna run all the churches

11:46.357 --> 11:47.924
in Brighton Park
that offer Mass in Spanish.

11:47.968 --> 11:49.447
Make a list. I'll take the top,

11:49.491 --> 11:50.797
you take the bottom,
we'll meet in the middle.

11:50.840 --> 11:53.277
- I like that.
It's a plan.

11:55.845 --> 11:57.455
- Anything?

11:57.499 --> 11:58.935
- No, ma'am.

11:58.979 --> 12:01.895
- This is stupid.

12:01.938 --> 12:03.505
- Might as well knock out
the last few.

12:03.548 --> 12:06.987
I'll be happy to let you know
you're wasted my damn time.

12:07.030 --> 12:08.510
Let's go.

12:08.553 --> 12:09.816
Her name's Karla de Leon.

12:09.859 --> 12:11.818
You sure about that?

12:11.861 --> 12:13.776
I said I haven't
seen this woman.

12:13.820 --> 12:15.430
- 'Cause we think
she's in real trouble.

12:15.473 --> 12:17.606
[door opens and closes]

12:17.649 --> 12:19.869
- Hola, Padre Francisco.
Un día bendito.

12:22.829 --> 12:24.569
- Well, I'll keep an eye out.

12:26.267 --> 12:28.704
- Esta es una
iglesia santuario.

12:28.748 --> 12:31.489
- A what?
- No, no, you heard me.

12:31.533 --> 12:33.535
This is a sanctuary church.

12:33.578 --> 12:35.798
You know it's a crime to
harbor undocumented immigrants.

12:35.842 --> 12:37.321
- Even here.

12:37.365 --> 12:38.801
- I've never had any trouble
with ICE--

12:38.845 --> 12:40.542
- Yeah, well, that's a courtesy
on our part.

12:40.585 --> 12:41.978
We can notify ICE at any time

12:42.022 --> 12:44.024
so why don't you take a look
at that picture again.

12:44.067 --> 12:47.027
[tense music]

12:47.070 --> 12:49.725
♪

12:49.769 --> 12:51.379
- She has nothing.

12:51.422 --> 12:52.554
No one.

12:52.597 --> 12:56.514
She said bad people
had sold her baby.

12:56.558 --> 12:58.299
- Where is she?

12:58.342 --> 13:04.000
♪

13:04.044 --> 13:05.915
- Please, only women
inside our shelter.

13:05.959 --> 13:14.358
♪

13:14.402 --> 13:15.882
- Karla de Leon.

13:15.925 --> 13:17.971
It's okay.

13:18.014 --> 13:21.061
You're not in trouble,
all right?

13:21.104 --> 13:23.846
I can help you find your baby.

13:28.633 --> 13:30.635
Do you know this woman?

13:30.679 --> 13:32.463
- Sofia.

13:32.507 --> 13:35.336
She is...okay?

13:35.379 --> 13:39.079
- No, Sofia fue asesinada.

13:39.122 --> 13:40.863
- The--the baby?

13:40.907 --> 13:43.866
[soft music]

13:43.910 --> 13:45.781
♪

13:45.825 --> 13:48.479
- I need you to tell me
everything.

13:52.570 --> 13:54.964
- Two months ago,
I was pregnant.

13:55.008 --> 13:57.662
At home, in Guatemala.

13:57.706 --> 14:00.056
These men, they--they bring me.

14:00.100 --> 14:03.016
- Te reclutaron.
- To come to America.

14:03.059 --> 14:05.801
- Hmm, they paid you?

14:05.845 --> 14:08.673
- I paid them.

14:08.717 --> 14:10.937
Everything I had.

14:10.980 --> 14:13.940
- Because they were providing
you with a service.

14:13.983 --> 14:15.202
They promise you
you'd give birth

14:15.245 --> 14:17.378
to an American citizen
which would put you

14:17.421 --> 14:21.861
on the path to citizenship
yourself, yeah?

14:21.904 --> 14:25.952
- They were going.
to sell our babies.

14:25.995 --> 14:29.433
And they told us of a mother
who went back home to Guatemala

14:29.477 --> 14:31.609
and she--she tried to--

14:31.653 --> 14:35.396
to make noise
about what had happened.

14:35.439 --> 14:37.789
And they--

14:39.008 --> 14:41.968
- They made her disappear?

14:42.011 --> 14:45.667
- So we were all
too scared to do anything.

14:45.710 --> 14:48.452
All except one.

14:48.496 --> 14:51.020
- Sofia.

14:51.847 --> 14:53.936
- She told me
she would get out.

14:53.980 --> 14:55.938
Somehow.

14:59.724 --> 15:03.163
After I had my baby,
they took me to the airport

15:03.206 --> 15:05.861
with a ticket home.

15:05.905 --> 15:09.430
They said they would kill me
if they saw me again.

15:11.562 --> 15:14.391
- But still, you couldn't
get on that plane?

15:14.435 --> 15:16.611
- Could you?

15:19.614 --> 15:22.051
- Who did this?

15:23.923 --> 15:27.927
David Cardona, DOB 2 March '92.

15:27.970 --> 15:29.493
Male Hispanic, 6'5.

15:29.537 --> 15:31.756
He runs the day-to-day
operations of the baby farm.

15:31.800 --> 15:33.933
He's got a boss,
goes by "Flaco."

15:33.976 --> 15:35.760
Now, Karla's only
seen him a couple times

15:35.804 --> 15:38.589
but apparently everybody
is scared of Flaco.

15:38.633 --> 15:41.027
- So we're thinking Sofia
somehow escaped this baby mill

15:41.070 --> 15:42.985
and these guys went after her.
- According to Karla,

15:43.029 --> 15:44.813
Cardona would have led
the search for Sofia

15:44.856 --> 15:46.510
and could have
pulled the trigger, too.

15:46.554 --> 15:48.773
- You guys, I got him.
He's in the CTA system.

15:48.817 --> 15:50.906
Swipes his card every
afternoon on the L

15:50.950 --> 15:52.995
and then transfers
to the 52 bus at Midway

15:53.039 --> 15:54.692
either at Kedzie, St. Louis,
or California.

15:54.736 --> 15:57.043
- That's our window.

15:57.086 --> 16:00.568
[train rumbling]

16:00.611 --> 16:03.527
- Orange line's
coming into Kedzie.

16:03.571 --> 16:06.617
[tense music]

16:06.661 --> 16:13.668
♪

16:19.239 --> 16:22.024
- Got eyes on Cardona.
I think he made me.

16:22.068 --> 16:24.679
David Cardona, Chicago PD.
Get your hands in the air.

16:24.722 --> 16:26.724
♪

16:26.768 --> 16:29.814
Get your hands up.

16:29.858 --> 16:32.208
- [grunts]
- Whoa, whoa! Get down--

16:33.079 --> 16:34.776
5021 Henry, 10-1, 10-1.

16:34.819 --> 16:36.256
Shots fired at police,
offender going northbound.

16:36.299 --> 16:38.519
- Go get him, go get him.
- Two blocks, headed for you.

16:38.562 --> 16:40.825
- Get back!
- Cardona, drop your weapon!

16:42.001 --> 16:44.960
[dramatic music]

16:45.004 --> 16:47.223
- I'm in foot pursuit
on the 4700 block of Homan.

16:47.267 --> 16:50.661
Stop! Police!

16:53.925 --> 16:55.014
Cardona!

16:56.798 --> 16:57.973
Stop!

16:58.017 --> 17:00.671
[grunts]

17:00.715 --> 17:01.716
[groans]

17:03.892 --> 17:07.635
[gunshots]

17:07.678 --> 17:09.854
[gasps]

17:09.898 --> 17:13.119
[gunshots]

17:13.162 --> 17:14.642
[gun clicks]

17:14.685 --> 17:20.082
♪

17:20.126 --> 17:23.651
[grunts] [gunshots]

17:23.694 --> 17:25.000
- Kim!

17:25.044 --> 17:28.569
- [breathing heavily]

17:28.612 --> 17:34.749
♪

17:34.792 --> 17:36.620
5021 Eddie.

17:36.664 --> 17:39.058
Shots fired by the offender
and the police.

17:39.101 --> 17:41.625
Offender down.

17:41.669 --> 17:43.671
DOA.

17:43.714 --> 17:47.718
[dramatic music]

17:51.113 --> 17:51.331
.

17:51.374 --> 17:52.767
- So you good?
- Yeah.

17:52.810 --> 17:53.768
- Hey, Kim.
- Yeah?

17:53.811 --> 17:55.074
- You all right?

17:55.117 --> 17:56.727
- Yeah.
- Okay.

17:56.771 --> 17:58.512
Talked to the street deputy?
IRT?

17:58.555 --> 18:00.122
- Yeah, I mean,
they got to do their thing,

18:00.166 --> 18:02.298
but they made it clear
this one's pretty cut and dry.

18:02.342 --> 18:03.647
- I vouched for that, too.

18:03.691 --> 18:05.649
- All right.
And Cardona's weapon?

18:05.693 --> 18:07.303
- Not a match.
Whoever killed Sofia

18:07.347 --> 18:09.305
fired .38s from a revolver.

18:09.349 --> 18:11.046
Cardona fired .45s.

18:11.090 --> 18:13.483
- So we got nothing we didn't
already have this morning.

18:13.527 --> 18:15.703
Got no confirmation
on Sofia's killer,

18:15.746 --> 18:18.532
got no leads on where to find
the other women.

18:18.575 --> 18:20.447
- One point of interest.
We pulled a burner phone

18:20.490 --> 18:22.405
off Cardona's body.
- All right, well, press for

18:22.449 --> 18:23.667
any data you can get.

18:23.711 --> 18:26.148
Text messages,
pings that put Cardona

18:26.192 --> 18:28.498
at the scene of the crime--
any breadcrumbs,

18:28.542 --> 18:31.458
'cause we don't have a lot else
going on right now.

18:36.637 --> 18:38.160
- Adam.

18:38.204 --> 18:41.511
- Yeah?

18:41.555 --> 18:43.687
- Thank you.

18:43.731 --> 18:45.385
- Doing my job.

18:45.428 --> 18:47.735
- Look, I get it.

18:47.778 --> 18:49.780
Clearly, you're still
pissed at me.

18:49.824 --> 18:51.391
But, come on, you are
gonna have to find a way

18:51.434 --> 18:55.612
to let me back in
at some point.

18:55.656 --> 18:57.788
- Gonna need a new jacket.

18:57.832 --> 19:00.791
[dramatic music]

19:00.835 --> 19:07.842
♪

19:31.257 --> 19:33.868
- [sighs]

19:33.911 --> 19:36.392
- [screams]

19:36.436 --> 19:38.786
- Makayla?

19:38.829 --> 19:39.830
Makayla?

19:39.874 --> 19:41.615
- They're here!
- Who's here?

19:41.658 --> 19:43.921
- They're here.
They're coming to get me.

19:43.965 --> 19:46.576
- Hey, hey, it's just me.

19:46.620 --> 19:48.230
Oh, my gosh, okay.

19:48.274 --> 19:49.753
No one's here.

19:49.797 --> 19:52.582
No one's here.
- They are.

19:52.626 --> 19:54.280
- You're okay.

19:54.323 --> 19:57.413
Nobody's here.
It's a nightmare.

19:57.457 --> 20:00.547
[softly] Hey, it's me.

20:00.590 --> 20:02.766
It's me.
It's just a nightmare.

20:02.810 --> 20:04.507
You're here with me.

20:04.551 --> 20:06.727
Can you go back to sleep?

20:06.770 --> 20:08.250
- [whimpers]
- I'll stay right here, okay?

20:08.294 --> 20:10.165
- Okay.
- Okay.

20:12.341 --> 20:14.517
Okay.

20:14.561 --> 20:16.258
It's okay.

20:16.302 --> 20:18.434
[softly] You're okay.

20:18.478 --> 20:21.263
You're okay.

20:21.307 --> 20:23.352
[whispers] You're okay.

20:23.396 --> 20:25.267
- She's had a couple
of these episodes?

20:25.311 --> 20:27.487
- Yeah. Not like this, though.

20:27.530 --> 20:28.618
Yeah.

20:28.662 --> 20:30.272
- Well, these aren't
nightmares, Kim,

20:30.316 --> 20:31.839
they're night terrors.

20:31.882 --> 20:34.929
Makayla, she's seen things
kids should not see.

20:34.972 --> 20:37.323
She watched her mother die,

20:37.366 --> 20:39.455
her father hunted her.

20:39.499 --> 20:42.763
The level of trauma here
is extraordinary.

20:42.806 --> 20:45.331
This was her only mechanism
to cope.

20:45.374 --> 20:47.811
- Well, we've both
seen some things.

20:47.855 --> 20:50.945
- That leads me
to my next subject,

20:50.988 --> 20:52.512
you.

20:52.555 --> 20:53.817
- Me?

20:53.861 --> 20:56.820
- Makayla knows what you do
for a living, Kim.

20:56.864 --> 20:58.605
Knows, on some level,
what you're up against

20:58.648 --> 21:00.389
every time you walk out
the door.

21:00.433 --> 21:01.651
- I don't share any of that
with her.

21:01.695 --> 21:04.480
- Well, you don't have to.
It's who you are.

21:04.524 --> 21:06.613
Makayla's seen you
with a gun in your hand, Kim.

21:06.656 --> 21:10.443
She's seen you take on people
who are trying to hurt you.

21:10.486 --> 21:13.272
It's feeding this,
because Makayla knows

21:13.315 --> 21:16.927
if something happens to you,
what happens to her?

21:16.971 --> 21:18.538
You're all she's got.

21:18.581 --> 21:22.759
[phone buzzing]

21:22.803 --> 21:25.022
- I have to go. I'm sorry.

21:25.066 --> 21:30.724
♪

21:30.767 --> 21:32.421
- So techs busted into
the burner

21:32.465 --> 21:33.727
we found on Cardona.
- Kay.

21:33.770 --> 21:35.511
- We found an outgoing text
setting up a meet

21:35.555 --> 21:37.470
three days
before Sofia was killed.

21:37.513 --> 21:39.385
Strip mall, Garfield Park.

21:39.428 --> 21:41.735
So we scanned the site
and we got David Cardona

21:41.778 --> 21:43.345
handing a bag of something
off to this guy.

21:43.389 --> 21:44.912
- And we're thinking
that's Flaco, the boss?

21:44.955 --> 21:47.001
- That was the theory,
but we got the guy's plate.

21:47.044 --> 21:51.048
- So we ran the plate and
the car's registered to him.

21:51.092 --> 21:52.963
- Doesn't look like
a "Flaco" to me.

21:53.007 --> 21:54.704
- Nope,
it's Bruce Alan Wegner.

21:54.748 --> 21:57.272
Date of birth 3/30/71.

21:57.316 --> 21:59.274
He's a doctor.

21:59.318 --> 22:01.842
- Highly respected OB-GYN.
Or he was.

22:01.885 --> 22:03.539
Got his license revoked
last year.

22:03.583 --> 22:06.368
Got caught prescribing
opioids to himself. Wow.

22:06.412 --> 22:08.936
- Pick him up.

22:08.979 --> 22:12.896
[phone buzzing]

22:12.940 --> 22:15.290
- Your house is a gold mine,
Bruce.

22:15.334 --> 22:16.857
- Was it the rats
or the roaches?

22:16.900 --> 22:18.032
- Gynecological instruments,

22:18.075 --> 22:20.991
which you're no longer
licensed to use.

22:21.035 --> 22:23.298
Prenatal vitamins,
pregnancy meds,

22:23.342 --> 22:25.300
all the prescriptions
written in the name of

22:25.344 --> 22:27.737
a Dr. Adrienne Cross.

22:27.781 --> 22:29.913
- My former partner.

22:29.957 --> 22:31.872
She was amazing to me.

22:31.915 --> 22:34.744
Generous, kind,
in my lowest days.

22:34.788 --> 22:37.051
So, naturally,

22:37.094 --> 22:39.749
I stole her letterhead
and used it to forge scripts.

22:39.793 --> 22:40.924
- Which you then used

22:40.968 --> 22:43.013
to provide late-term
pre-natal care

22:43.057 --> 22:45.407
at an off-the-books baby farm.

22:45.451 --> 22:47.627
You're an active participant
in a criminal conspiracy

22:47.670 --> 22:48.758
that ended in the murder

22:48.802 --> 22:51.413
of a 17-year-old girl.
[phone buzzes]

22:51.457 --> 22:53.937
If-- [phone buzzes, stops]
If you work with me,

22:53.981 --> 22:55.591
I'll get you into
court-ordered rehab.

22:55.635 --> 22:57.376
- I can't do that.

22:57.419 --> 22:58.681
- Well, then you're
looking at prison.

22:58.725 --> 23:01.771
- [chuckles]
Thing is, prison, I'm alive.

23:01.815 --> 23:04.861
I talk, I'm dead.
[phone buzzes]

23:04.905 --> 23:06.428
- [sighs]

23:06.472 --> 23:07.777
Burgess.

23:11.128 --> 23:12.434
What?

23:12.478 --> 23:14.131
- Makayla fell asleep in class.

23:14.175 --> 23:15.959
- Yeah, she's been
waking up at night.

23:16.003 --> 23:18.440
- And then woke up, sort of.
- Sort of?

23:18.484 --> 23:20.790
- Woke up screaming.
- Oh, God.

23:20.834 --> 23:23.140
- I don't think the children
were trying to be cruel.

23:23.184 --> 23:26.405
It was startling,
maybe a little scary,

23:26.448 --> 23:28.842
and some of them may have
laughed at her.

23:28.885 --> 23:31.061
- She locked herself in.
Won't budge.

23:31.105 --> 23:32.541
- Right through there.
- Okay, thanks.

23:32.585 --> 23:34.021
Could I get--

23:34.064 --> 23:37.024
[emotional music]

23:37.067 --> 23:39.722
Hey, buddy. It's me, okay?

23:39.766 --> 23:46.816
♪

23:49.819 --> 23:52.431
You don't have to
come out or anything but

23:52.474 --> 23:54.389
can you let me know
that you're okay?

24:16.716 --> 24:18.457
[phone buzzes]

24:27.466 --> 24:29.946
- I just want things
the way they were.

24:32.166 --> 24:35.038
- I know. I know you do.

24:35.082 --> 24:37.127
- I just want my mommy.

24:39.869 --> 24:42.002
- And it's not fair.

24:42.045 --> 24:45.527
You got me and it's--
it's just not the same.

24:47.834 --> 24:51.533
All I can tell you, Makayla,

24:51.577 --> 24:54.667
is that you're safe.

24:54.710 --> 24:56.712
And you're so loved.

24:59.193 --> 25:01.543
And I would--

25:01.587 --> 25:04.067
I would really appreciate it
if you would just

25:04.111 --> 25:06.722
let me see you?
You know, let me know

25:06.766 --> 25:08.463
that you're ok--
[click]

25:19.822 --> 25:22.042
Hi.

25:35.969 --> 25:39.102
I keep telling everybody
how brave you are.

25:39.146 --> 25:41.017
But you shouldn't
have to be brave.

25:41.061 --> 25:43.933
You're too little to be brave.

25:43.977 --> 25:47.807
♪

26:13.006 --> 26:13.223
.

26:13.267 --> 26:16.618
- I got pregnant last year.

26:16.662 --> 26:18.228
- Congratulations.

26:18.272 --> 26:20.100
- Hah.

26:20.143 --> 26:23.494
Didn't work out.

26:23.538 --> 26:25.322
- I'm sorry to hear that.

26:25.366 --> 26:27.150
- Yeah.

26:27.194 --> 26:29.979
I got morning sickness
really badly.

26:32.112 --> 26:34.549
What saved me was this.
I found it at your house.

26:34.593 --> 26:37.639
- Promethazine.
Does the trick.

26:37.683 --> 26:40.033
- Yeah.

26:40.076 --> 26:41.991
These drugs we found, nitro--

26:42.035 --> 26:43.645
- Nitrofurantoin.

26:43.689 --> 26:45.212
For UTIs.

26:50.304 --> 26:53.263
- Everyone in this building...

26:53.307 --> 26:56.615
they all think
you're just some junkie.

26:56.658 --> 26:59.487
You know, a doctor
who betrayed his oath,

26:59.530 --> 27:01.707
make some quick cash,
buy drugs.

27:06.320 --> 27:08.061
I don't think that's right.

27:08.104 --> 27:09.628
- No?

27:11.804 --> 27:13.719
- I think your marching orders

27:13.762 --> 27:15.372
from your employers
are pretty simple.

27:15.416 --> 27:18.680
You keep the women alive,

27:18.724 --> 27:23.076
you get the babies,
and the rest--

27:23.119 --> 27:27.515
But you treated these women,
these throwaways

27:27.558 --> 27:30.605
like queens.

27:30.649 --> 27:35.262
[soft emotional music]

27:35.305 --> 27:38.134
I don't think you ever
stopped caring, Dr. Wegner.

27:38.178 --> 27:45.141
♪

27:45.185 --> 27:49.406
- I hate myself
for being a part of this.

27:49.450 --> 27:51.365
- And so you worked and worked

27:51.408 --> 27:55.586
to make sure that these babies
and these women were healthy.

27:55.630 --> 27:57.458
But the end result--

27:57.501 --> 28:04.857
♪

28:04.900 --> 28:07.207
- [sobs quietly]

28:07.250 --> 28:10.166
There's no greater pain.

28:11.254 --> 28:14.214
- Dr. Wegner,

28:14.257 --> 28:16.520
you can end this.

28:16.564 --> 28:19.741
Right now.

28:19.785 --> 28:22.265
- [weeps quietly]

28:28.402 --> 28:30.404
- Sarge.

28:30.447 --> 28:32.580
The doc doesn't know
who Flaco is.

28:32.623 --> 28:35.888
Never met him,
never heard his real name.

28:35.931 --> 28:38.325
But he gave us this guy.

28:38.368 --> 28:39.761
- "New Bond Family Services"?

28:39.805 --> 28:41.589
- It's an adoption agency
out in the 'burbs.

28:41.632 --> 28:44.592
It's legit on paper.
Wilson Richards is the CEO.

28:44.635 --> 28:46.246
Him and the doc go way back.

28:46.289 --> 28:48.552
He's the one who recruited
the doc into this thing.

28:48.596 --> 28:49.728
Richards is the broker.

28:49.771 --> 28:51.773
He's the bridge
between the baby farm

28:51.817 --> 28:53.862
and the couples looking
to adopt an infant.

28:53.906 --> 28:56.778
Richards buys the babies
from Flaco for 40 grand.

28:56.822 --> 28:59.215
Charges 80 for adoption.

28:59.259 --> 29:01.827
- Pay him a visit.

29:01.870 --> 29:04.830
[dramatic music]

29:04.873 --> 29:08.834
♪

29:08.877 --> 29:10.923
- Can I help you?
- Chicago PD, ma'am.

29:10.966 --> 29:12.794
Where's Wilson Richards?
- In his office.

29:12.838 --> 29:14.361
- Put your hands on your desk.
Don't touch your computer.

29:14.404 --> 29:15.884
Do you understand me?

29:15.928 --> 29:17.451
Okay, I need you two to leave.
- We have an appointment.

29:17.494 --> 29:18.626
- I understand.
I need you to go right now.

29:18.669 --> 29:19.932
Come on, let's go.

29:19.975 --> 29:21.890
- Chicago PD.
- What is this?

29:21.934 --> 29:23.544
- Wilson Richards,
you're under arrest.

29:23.587 --> 29:24.937
- On what grounds?
- For financing

29:24.980 --> 29:27.287
the kidnapping
of tender-age children.

29:27.330 --> 29:29.506
- Babies.

29:29.550 --> 29:31.291
- Dear God.

29:31.334 --> 29:34.337
- Turn around and put
your hands behind your back.

29:37.863 --> 29:39.821
- So Richards is talking?
- Oh, yeah.

29:39.865 --> 29:43.303
Yeah, he folded
like a lawn chair.

29:43.346 --> 29:45.609
- This is Flaco,
AKA Javier Ortiz.

29:45.653 --> 29:47.960
Date of birth, 2/17/76.

29:48.003 --> 29:49.831
This is the man that
killed Sofia Perez.

29:49.875 --> 29:52.268
- Ortiz and Richards,
that's the partnership.

29:52.312 --> 29:54.488
The nexus of this whole thing.
We got receipts.

29:54.531 --> 29:56.664
- Ortiz forwards photos
of the pregnant recruits

29:56.707 --> 29:58.318
from Guatemala
to Wilson Richards,

29:58.361 --> 30:00.233
and we got all those emails
off of Richards' laptop.

30:00.276 --> 30:02.235
- Ortiz is all over
social media wearing

30:02.278 --> 30:04.324
the sweatshirt from the video
of Sofia's murder.

30:04.367 --> 30:05.542
It's a clear match.

30:05.586 --> 30:06.892
- Went down pretty much
like we thought.

30:06.935 --> 30:08.850
According to Ortiz,
Sofia escaped,

30:08.894 --> 30:10.896
Cordona and some other
low-levels, they give chase.

30:10.939 --> 30:12.854
Cordona caught up with Sofia
on the rooftop.

30:12.898 --> 30:14.508
They struggled, she fell,

30:14.551 --> 30:16.205
survived somehow.

30:16.249 --> 30:18.338
They panic and called Ortiz
who was around the corner.

30:18.381 --> 30:19.774
- And Ortiz
came in to finish it,

30:19.818 --> 30:22.516
and they shut the place down
to cover their tracks.

30:22.559 --> 30:23.604
So where did they go?

30:23.647 --> 30:24.910
- New City.
Wilson Richards bought

30:24.953 --> 30:27.738
the property on a foreclosure
couple years back.

30:27.782 --> 30:29.392
Told Ortiz to lay low there.

30:29.436 --> 30:30.654
- And we believe
the other women

30:30.698 --> 30:31.873
are being held there, correct?

30:31.917 --> 30:33.527
- Correct.

30:33.570 --> 30:37.879
- All right, this could go down
real bad, real fast.

30:37.923 --> 30:39.533
Go get a schematic
of that building

30:39.576 --> 30:42.492
so we can find the best way in.

30:42.536 --> 30:46.409
You go in dark,
you go in quiet.

30:46.453 --> 30:48.411
Strap up.

30:48.455 --> 30:51.414
[dramatic music]

30:51.458 --> 30:58.465
♪

31:51.648 --> 31:54.042
- Don't you dare, man.

31:54.086 --> 31:56.001
Get on the ground.

31:56.044 --> 31:57.959
- How many more of you
are there?

31:58.003 --> 32:01.963
- Two.
- Two including Flaco?

32:02.007 --> 32:03.443
You got him?
- Yeah, I got him.

32:03.486 --> 32:04.879
I'll get your six.

32:06.663 --> 32:07.795
Stand up.

32:07.838 --> 32:14.628
♪

32:14.671 --> 32:16.978
[rapid gunfire]

32:17.022 --> 32:20.764
[gunfire]

32:20.808 --> 32:22.331
- Jay, moving.

32:30.470 --> 32:31.601
- Hey!

32:31.645 --> 32:33.081
- [grunts]

32:33.125 --> 32:39.479
♪

32:39.522 --> 32:41.698
- Jay, I got movement.
- Okay, I got him. Go.

32:54.189 --> 32:55.582
- It's okay, it's okay.

32:55.625 --> 32:57.018
Policía, come on.

32:57.062 --> 32:59.020
Come on.

32:59.064 --> 33:01.066
Down the stairs. Okay.

33:01.109 --> 33:03.416
Hay una más.
- One more, where?

33:03.459 --> 33:05.635
- No se. Flaco, he has her.

33:05.679 --> 33:12.381
♪

33:15.080 --> 33:16.603
- Chicago PD!

33:16.646 --> 33:17.734
- Flaco, put it down!

33:17.778 --> 33:19.562
[rapid gunfire]

33:23.088 --> 33:25.960
[dramatic music]

33:26.004 --> 33:33.054
♪

33:33.098 --> 33:35.752
- [muffled]

33:39.582 --> 33:40.888
[whispering] Kim.

33:40.931 --> 33:43.064
Kim!

33:43.108 --> 33:46.850
You all right?

33:46.894 --> 33:48.156
Okay, move on three.

33:48.200 --> 33:49.157
Yeah?
- Yeah.

33:49.201 --> 33:51.029
- One, two, go.

33:53.770 --> 33:55.642
All right, go around.

33:55.685 --> 33:59.080
♪

33:59.124 --> 34:01.648
- No, no, por favor.

34:01.691 --> 34:03.867
[sobbing]

34:03.911 --> 34:05.086
No!

34:05.130 --> 34:07.132
Por favor, mi bebé, no!
- Let her go.

34:07.175 --> 34:08.524
Drop the weapon, Flaco.
- No!

34:10.570 --> 34:11.571
- I'll kill her.

34:11.614 --> 34:12.746
That's on you.
- No!

34:12.789 --> 34:14.704
- Drop that weapon,
you let her go.

34:14.748 --> 34:16.228
Now!
- Por favor!

34:16.271 --> 34:17.577
- Drop the weapon.

34:17.620 --> 34:20.014
[tense music]

34:20.058 --> 34:21.581
- [grunts]
- Drop it!

34:21.624 --> 34:24.758
♪

34:24.801 --> 34:26.064
- [groans]

34:27.239 --> 34:29.067
- Let her go...

34:31.069 --> 34:34.115
Or I blow your head
all over this room.

34:36.161 --> 34:37.205
- Kay.

34:38.598 --> 34:40.469
- Drop the weapon.
Get on your knees.

34:41.905 --> 34:43.864
Hands above your head.

34:43.907 --> 34:50.914
♪

35:04.014 --> 35:04.189
.

35:04.232 --> 35:05.407
- Hi.
- Hey.

35:05.451 --> 35:07.148
- You heard from DCFS?

35:07.192 --> 35:09.585
- I did.
They reached out to the family

35:09.629 --> 35:11.587
that bought Karla de Leon's
daughter.

35:11.631 --> 35:13.589
They picked up the baby
earlier today,

35:13.633 --> 35:16.157
and they're gonna return her
to Karla tonight.

35:16.201 --> 35:17.245
- Good.

35:17.289 --> 35:18.986
The other mothers
are safe, too, so...

35:19.029 --> 35:22.163
- Yeah. Nice to see
the good guys get a win.

35:22.207 --> 35:23.469
- Yeah.

35:27.212 --> 35:28.300
- You all right?

35:28.343 --> 35:29.692
- Yeah, I'm fine.

35:36.046 --> 35:38.658
We were taking fire
and I just--I--

35:43.184 --> 35:44.707
I hesitated.

35:44.751 --> 35:47.623
Just froze.

35:47.667 --> 35:49.190
I mean, I could've
lost the hostage,

35:49.234 --> 35:50.278
I could've got
one of the guys hurt,

35:50.322 --> 35:51.714
I could've--
- But you didn't.

35:51.758 --> 35:54.021
- 'Cause I got lucky.

35:55.501 --> 35:59.331
[whispers] I got...scared.

35:59.374 --> 36:00.593
I mean, not for me.

36:00.636 --> 36:02.203
I didn't get scared for me.
I got scared--

36:02.247 --> 36:04.031
- Because of Makayla.
- Yeah.

36:07.513 --> 36:09.167
- You've given her

36:09.210 --> 36:12.561
a second chance at life
and that is worth protecting.

36:12.605 --> 36:15.042
And I wonder if this is why
the universe is telling you

36:15.085 --> 36:18.741
to name your guardian.
Your backup.

36:18.785 --> 36:21.179
I wonder if you'd
hesitate the same way

36:21.222 --> 36:23.398
if you had that peace of mind.

36:26.706 --> 36:29.709
Maybe.

36:29.752 --> 36:31.624
- Burgess.
- What?

36:31.667 --> 36:33.669
- Anybody would be honored
to participate

36:33.713 --> 36:37.543
in what you're doing with her.

36:37.586 --> 36:39.675
- Thanks.

36:39.719 --> 36:42.200
- Don't even think about
picking me.

36:44.245 --> 36:45.681
- Copy you.

36:48.554 --> 36:50.120
Night, Sarge.

36:50.164 --> 36:52.471
- See ya.

37:06.615 --> 37:08.574
[knocking on door]

37:12.534 --> 37:13.535
- Hey.

37:13.579 --> 37:14.667
- Thanks for coming.

37:14.710 --> 37:17.147
- Well, you said
it was urgent, so...

37:18.888 --> 37:20.325
That your shower curtain?

37:20.368 --> 37:23.415
- It's my former shower
curtain, yeah.

37:24.894 --> 37:27.419
- Hmm.

37:27.462 --> 37:28.594
- Makayla's asleep.

37:28.637 --> 37:30.465
Do you mind if we
talk out here?

37:30.509 --> 37:32.250
- Not at all.
What's going on?

37:32.293 --> 37:34.643
- Okay, yeah, yeah, yeah.
Um...

37:38.734 --> 37:41.128
I'm naming you as my custodian.

37:41.171 --> 37:44.479
In the adoption.

37:44.523 --> 37:45.828
Like, if anything
happens to me,

37:45.872 --> 37:50.442
you're the one who's gonna
take care of Makayla.

37:50.485 --> 37:52.226
- I'm a little confused.

37:52.270 --> 37:53.445
I mean, you remember
what's been going on?

37:53.488 --> 37:54.837
The questions
you've had about me?

37:54.881 --> 37:56.491
I mean, things haven't been
too good between us.

37:56.535 --> 37:58.754
- I know.

37:58.798 --> 38:01.453
- Okay, so is it about that
or is it about this case?

38:01.496 --> 38:02.671
What went down with Ortiz?
- No, it's not about

38:02.715 --> 38:03.890
either of those things.
- Okay, why would

38:03.933 --> 38:04.934
you do that then?
- Because we were supposed

38:04.978 --> 38:06.849
to have a baby together, dummy.

38:06.893 --> 38:09.852
[emotional music]

38:09.896 --> 38:12.812
♪

38:12.855 --> 38:16.468
Because we're family.

38:16.511 --> 38:17.599
Because...

38:20.646 --> 38:24.606
You and I are a lot of things,

38:24.650 --> 38:26.739
including pretty screwed up.

38:26.782 --> 38:28.349
- Hah.

38:28.393 --> 38:29.481
- Who knows
if we'll ever really

38:29.524 --> 38:31.918
get our act together but...

38:34.486 --> 38:37.750
Her last name
is Burgess now, Adam.

38:37.793 --> 38:39.839
And, um,

38:39.882 --> 38:41.710
one thing that we can be,

38:41.754 --> 38:43.712
you and I, is--

38:43.756 --> 38:45.453
is we can be this

38:45.497 --> 38:46.759
whole, big, round thing

38:46.802 --> 38:49.457
that can surround
and protect her.

38:49.501 --> 38:53.374
You know, even if Makayla
doesn't know it exists.

38:53.418 --> 38:56.203
And I need that.

38:56.246 --> 38:58.727
That's the only way
that I can do this.

38:58.771 --> 38:59.902
Be a good mom and

38:59.946 --> 39:03.689
be the kind of cop
that I need to be.

39:03.732 --> 39:05.908
I need that.

39:12.306 --> 39:14.961
Obviously, you can say no.

39:15.004 --> 39:16.658
But I'm--could you
just think about it?

39:16.702 --> 39:19.748
- I don't need
to think about it.

39:19.792 --> 39:22.795
The answer is yes, of course.

39:25.450 --> 39:27.626
I'm honored that you'd ask me.

39:27.669 --> 39:32.370
♪

39:32.413 --> 39:33.893
So, what, what do we do?
Do I sign something?

39:33.936 --> 39:35.373
Do we shake on it?
I don't know.

39:35.416 --> 39:37.287
What's the next step here?

39:37.331 --> 39:38.506
- Shake.

39:47.515 --> 39:49.474
- Cool.

40:13.498 --> 40:16.457
- Come here, bear. Come on.

40:18.633 --> 40:20.026
Actually,

40:20.069 --> 40:21.723
I got you something.

40:23.812 --> 40:26.075
These are called trouble dolls.

40:26.119 --> 40:28.730
And you are gonna put them
under your pillow

40:28.774 --> 40:30.558
and when you wake up
in the morning,

40:30.602 --> 40:31.733
you know what?

40:31.777 --> 40:33.648
They've taken
all your troubles.

40:33.692 --> 40:35.998
So your only job is to rest.

40:36.042 --> 40:37.913
How cool is that?

40:37.957 --> 40:40.916
- Really cool.
- Yeah.

40:40.960 --> 40:44.311
- Thank you.

40:44.354 --> 40:46.095
- I think that's a good order.

40:46.139 --> 40:49.838
Can I get one?

40:49.882 --> 40:51.449
You're nice.

40:51.492 --> 40:53.451
And now, sleep.

40:57.716 --> 40:59.892
Cozy?

41:04.070 --> 41:05.593
Good night, Makayla.

41:05.637 --> 41:06.942
- Good night.

41:06.986 --> 41:13.993
♪

41:52.553 --> 41:52.771
.

41:52.814 --> 41:55.730
[wolf howls]
